oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Model 1917 wool tunic of John William Cato
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This issued model 1917 wool tunic belonged to John William Cato. It is complete with collar discs and has the red honorable discharge chevron on upper left sleeve; one overseas chevron on lower left sleeve for 6 months service; and a wound chevron on the lower right sleeve. Cato was In gassed while serving with the infantry in France. He was born Dec. 28, 1895, and died April 10, 1973.
